    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics Model Years 1999-2000 - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS -
        Circuit Function And Diagnostics - Vehicle Retarder (VRE)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="7">
        <title>Vehicle Retarder (VRE)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f17503102" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figEG7/EG7325A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for Vehicle Retarder</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>On engines and vehicles equipped with an engine brake or a transmission retarder the VRE (Vehicle
                Retarder Circuit) circuits function is to control the relay or solenoids that turn the brake or retarder
                on and off. This circuit has many applications and can be wired in many configurations. The applicable
                wiring diagram for the application must be used for troubleshooting the circuit.
            </para>
            <para>See the appropriate wiring diagram:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503104">Exhaust Brake with WT Transmission Circuit
                            <xref refid="f17503104"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503105">Exhaust Brake with ABS, WTEC III Transmission Circuit
                            <xref refid="f17503105"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503106">Transmission Retarder Controls Wiring Circuits
                            <xref refid="f17503106"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503107">Transmission Retarder Controls Wiring Circuits
                            <xref refid="f17503107"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503108">Allison AT Retarder International&#174; /ABS Circuit
                            <xref refid="f17503108"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f17503103">VRE circuit
                            <xref refid="f17503103"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>The VRE circuit is generic and only describes the general function of this circuit. Chassis pin 47
                (VRE) is normally used to turn a relay or solenoid on and off by grounding the coil circuit of the
                relay. Chassis Pin 15 (EB) is used either as an ON/OFF switch for the engine brake or as a power source
                for the engine brake relay depending on application.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
